					<div id="elementor-tab-content-2148" class="elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix" data-tab="8" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="elementor-tab-title-2148" tabindex="0" hidden="hidden"><p><b>Post Date: February 2021<br>Location:&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://rttprod.wpengine.com/park-cities" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Park Cities Office</a></b></p><p><b>Job Summary:</b><br>Provides support to the branch office by assisting with administrative duties related to escrow closings.</p><p><b>Essential Functions:</b></p><p>Receipt contracts; send receipted page/contracts to selling &amp; listing agents; turn in orders; request buyer and seller information per contract; scan to commitment/HOA department; send commitment package to lender; order payoffs; contact with agents, new lenders, payoff lenders, clients for information and status; follow up when requested information has not yet been received; schedule closing appointments; prepare Closing Disclosures (CD); send CD to selling agent and listing agent; prepare closing package; fund file; disburse file (balance file, request checks from accounting, disburse checks to all parties); prepare file and send to shipping department</p><p><b>Typical Education:</b><br>High School diploma or equivalent</p><p><b>Typical Range of Experience:</b>&nbsp;<br>3 years’ experience in a related real estate or title field</p><p><b>Independence/Supervision:</b><br>Limited supervision</p><p><b>Reports to:</b><br>Escrow Officer and/or Branch Manager</p><p><b>Working Conditions or Accommodations:</b><br>May lift and/or move up to 10 pounds.</p><p><b>Knowledge and Skills/Technology Used:&nbsp; </b>Ability to multi-task and prioritize in a very busy environment; excellent customer service skills (must be willing to please our customers); strong work ethic; excellent computer skills; strong communication skills; self-starter/initiative; positive attitude; must be available to work overtime as needed</p><p><b>Disclaimer:</b>&nbsp;<br>The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed by people assigned to this classification. They are not to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties, and skills required of personnel so classified. All personnel may be required to perform duties outside of their normal responsibilities from time to time, as needed.</p><p>To apply for this position, please&nbsp;<a href="mailto:jobs@republictitle.com?subject=Republic Title - Experienced Escrow Officer - Application" target="_blank" rel="noopener">email</a>&nbsp;your resume to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:jobs@republictitle.com?subject=Republic Title - Experienced Escrow Officer - Application" target="_blank" rel="noopener">jobs@republictitle.com</a>.</p></div>
